                <h1>Malala Yousafzai: A Symbol of Courage and Education</h1>
                <p>Malala Yousafzai is a Pakistani education activist and the youngest Nobel Prize laureate. After surviving an attack by the Taliban for advocating girls' education, she became a global symbol of resilience. Malala continues to promote education and women's rights through her organization, the Malala Fund, inspiring millions worldwide.</p>
